name: Qualify Calendly Demo Requests with GPT-4 & Route to Saleshandy Sequences with Logs
description:
This n8n template captures every ‚ÄúRequest a Demo‚Äù booking in Calendly, uses OpenAI to score and qualify leads in real time, routes them into the correct Saleshandy sequence, and logs all data in Google Sheets for full GTM visibility.

## Use cases include:

Empowering SDR teams to focus on high-value demos
Providing growth marketers with reliable funnel metrics
Automating triage for B2B AE teams overwhelmed by demo requests

## Good to know

OpenAI GPT-4 calls cost based on token usage‚Äîyou can expect ~1,200 tokens per lead.
Calendly API rate-limits at 180 requests/min; consider batching if volume spikes.
Google Sheets writes are single-threaded; high-volume users may opt for Airtable or BigQuery.

## How it works
**Capture** ‚Äì Webhook node listens for every new ‚ÄúRequest a Demo‚Äù form submission in Calendly.

**Score** ‚Äì AI Agent node sends job title, company size, domain quality, and custom questions to OpenAI; returns a 1‚Äì10 score plus label (Qualified/Semi-qualified/Unqualified).

**Verify meeting** ‚Äì HTTP Request node confirms via the Calendly API that a slot was actually scheduled.

**Route** ‚Äì Switch node selects the appropriate Saleshandy sequence ID (Qualified, Nurture, Disqualify).

**Send** ‚Äì HTTP Request nodes add each prospect to the chosen Saleshandy sequence.

**Log** ‚Äì Google Sheets nodes write to three tabs (Qualified, Semi-qualified, Unqualified) with lead data, score, routing path, and timestamp.

## Prerequisites

n8n workspace
Accounts & API credentials for:
Calendly
OpenAI (GPT-4 or GPT-3.5)
Google Sheets
Saleshandy

## Step-by-Step Setup

**1. Import the n8n Template**
Upload the JSON file into your n8n workspace.

**2. Add Required Credentials**
In n8n ‚Üí Credentials, add:
Calendly: Personal Access Token (PAT)
OpenAI: API Key
Google Sheets: OAuth2 connection
Saleshandy: API Key

**3. Calendly Setup**
Go to Calendly Webhook Docs
Create a Routing Form in Calendly.
Generate your access token.
Use Postman or any API client to:
Make a POST request to create a webhook subscription.
Use your n8n webhook URL in the url field.
Add your Authorization token and extract the Organization ID.
Paste the webhook URL into the Calendly Routing Form.

**4. Set Your Saleshandy Sequences**
In n8n, locate the Set: Sequence IDs node.
Replace the placeholder text with:
Your actual Qualified
Semi-qualified
and Unqualified Saleshandy sequence step IDs.

**5. Configure Google Sheets**
Create a spreadsheet with the following tabs:
Qualified
Semi-qualified
Unqualified
In n8n, connect the three Google Sheets nodes to this file.


## Customising this workflow

**Adjust scoring logic** ‚Äì Modify the OpenAI prompt in the AI Agent node to weight ARR, industry, or headcount differently.

**Refine thresholds** ‚Äì Change the Switch node rules for score ranges (e.g., Qualified ‚â•8, Semi-qualified 5‚Äì7).

**Swap destinations** ‚Äì Edit HTTP Request nodes to integrate with your CRM or email platform instead of Saleshandy.

**Enhance logging** ‚Äì Replace Google Sheets with Airtable, BigQuery, or another analytics store.

**Add notifications** ‚Äì Insert Slack or Microsoft Teams nodes after routing to alert reps instantly.

options.systemMessage:
You are an AI scoring agent that evaluates user input data related to Calendly requests. Your goal is to analyze the provided user data and assign a single-digit numeric score ranging from -1 to 10, based on the quality, completeness, and validity of the input. Return only the numeric score as a single digit or -1, with no additional text or explanation.

Instructions:

Examine the user input data carefully.

Validate that all required fields are properly filled and formatted.

Assess the data quality and completeness.

Produce only one integer score between:

0 to 10 (single digit except for 10, which is two digits but acceptable as max score),

Or -1 if the input is invalid or unusable.

Return just the numeric value with no extra words or characters.

Output Format:

Return only a single integer value: -1 or a number from 0 to 10.

This instruction should ensure the AI only outputs the score itself. Let me know if you want it stricter to only single digit (0-9) and treat 10 differently!

## Unqualified Lead Logger
Stores disqualified leads and AI scores for GTM visibility and analysis.
‚Üí Scores ‚â§ 4
‚Üí Logged but not routed to cold email outreach campaigns

These updated names and sticky notes follow best practices for:

üëâ Descriptive, action-based node names

‚úÖ Clear purpose for each sticky note

üí° Easy for first-time users and reviewers in the Creator Hub

## Semiqualified Lead Logger
Appends or updates leads with moderate potential (scores between 5‚Äì6) for nurturing.
‚Üí Sheet: "Demo Requests"
‚Üí All fields mapped dynamically from form & AI Agent

## Qualified Lead Logger
Updates Google Sheet with qualified lead details, AI score, and other fields pulled from the Calendly form.
‚Üí Sheet: "Demo Requests"
‚Üí Match by: Email
üëâ Used for Sales-ready leads scoring 7 or above

## Meeting Status Switch
Evaluates the Calendly API response to see if the invitee booked a meeting.

If pagination.count === 0 ‚Üí route as Not Booked

If there‚Äôs at least 1 event ‚Üí path goes to Booked

Used for personalizing follow-up or filtering out no-shows.

## Lead Qualification & Logging
This section routes leads into segments based on the AI score and logs them into Google Sheets for visibility.

Route Lead by AI Score:
‚û§ If Score ‚â• 7 ‚Üí Qualified
‚û§ If Score ‚â§ 4 ‚Üí Unqualified
‚û§ Score between 5‚Äì6 ‚Üí Semiqualified

Log Lead to Google Sheet:
Saves all lead details + score + event status for reporting and follow-up.
Uses form responses to fill dynamic fields like name, email, budget, and interest area.

‚úÖ Keeps GTM & RevOps teams in sync
üìÅ Automatically updates existing rows (by email) or adds new ones

üß† This AI Agent scores leads from 1 to 10 using structured data from Calendly form submissions.

‚úÖ Scoring is based on:
- Email domain (business vs. free)
- Country code in phone number (geo-priority)
- Product/solution interest (single vs. multiple)
- Monthly usage volume
- Company size
- Monthly budget
- Additional notes (intent, urgency, discounts)

üåç If the phone country code is **not in the allowed list**, the agent returns `-1`.

üõ†Ô∏è Customizable Parameters:
- Approved country codes (in prompt)
- Usage volume thresholds
- Budget brackets
- Importance (weight) of each factor
- Definition of ‚Äúqualified lead‚Äù

üîß Edit the AI Agent node‚Äôs **system prompt** to tailor the logic to your company‚Äôs lead qualification needs.

üì¶ Model routing is handled via the **Model Selector node**, allowing use of Claude, GPT, Gemini, Mistral, or OpenRouter.

üéØ Use this to automate SDR prioritization, CRM enrichment, or sales pipeline segmentation.

## Calendly Webhook 

Triggers when someone submits the Calendly Routing Form.
Make sure this URL is added as a webhook in your Calendly form settings.
